1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,033
Edited at https://subtitletools.com

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:04,120
I must crush his will.

3
00:00:04,580 --> 00:00:07,970
His will to fight, his will to stand,

4
00:00:07,970 --> 00:00:09,440
his will to resist...

5
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:19,710
Let me demonstrate that all your hard
work and confidence mean nothing!

6
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:45,040
Victor x And x Loser

7
00:02:01,820 --> 00:02:02,640
He's fast...

8
00:02:03,130 --> 00:02:05,390
I had no time to dodge!

9
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,670
But I can still block his attacks!

10
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:12,690
Oh? He used Gyo?

11
00:02:13,480 --> 00:02:15,600
The moment I grasped his arm,

12
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:18,450
he focused his aura there to block my attack.

13
00:02:19,950 --> 00:02:21,050
Idiot!

14
00:02:21,050 --> 00:02:24,080
You think you've outwitted me now?!

15
00:02:34,370 --> 00:02:35,920
What's the matter?

16
00:02:35,920 --> 00:02:37,970
That was just a body blow.

17
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:41,170
If you focus your aura where I grab you,

18
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:43,970
you leave yourself open everywhere else.

19
00:02:43,970 --> 00:02:45,300
It's futile...

20
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:49,250
In fact, you're only making
it harder on yourself.

21
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:56,110
Bisky was right!

22
00:02:58,670 --> 00:03:00,740
You won't be smiling much longer!

23
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:09,400
One more hit to send you to hell!

24
00:03:15,450 --> 00:03:16,490
Impossible!

25
00:03:16,490 --> 00:03:18,180
That was the hardest hit so far!

26
00:03:18,180 --> 00:03:19,920
He shouldn't have been able to counter.

27
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:24,680
But since he did, that means he
kept the damage to a minimum.

28
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:29,730
In other words, he blocked me
without relying on aura.

29
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:33,250
He guessed I didn't intend to set off a bomb?

30
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,770
No, that wasn't a guess.

31
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,490
Hey, Bisky...

32
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:43,030
How does Genthru avoid being
burned by his own bombs?

33
00:03:44,110 --> 00:03:45,580
That's quite simple.

34
00:03:45,580 --> 00:03:50,700
He shrouds his hand in aura that's
stronger than the explosion.

35
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,290
Oh... I get it.

36
00:03:52,730 --> 00:03:56,290
It's a technique that requires
a large aura reserve.

37
00:03:57,580 --> 00:03:59,530
This is a good opportunity.

38
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:01,300
By now, you should be able to tell.

39
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:05,600
Excellent reaction!

40
00:04:05,600 --> 00:04:07,790
You've almost perfected Gyo.

41
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:09,560
One more time, then.

42
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,760
Huh?

43
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,250
Could you tell the difference?

44
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:17,040
Yeah, you used less aura the second time.

45
00:04:17,430 --> 00:04:19,330
Okay, you pass.

46
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:23,820
You'll have an easier time with him
if you can tell the difference.

47
00:04:24,580 --> 00:04:29,130
When Genthru prepares Little Flower,
he will shroud his hand with Gyo.

48
00:04:29,130 --> 00:04:33,780
If he's just faking and planning
to attack you somewhere else,

49
00:04:33,780 --> 00:04:35,970
he probably won't use Gyo.

50
00:04:37,030 --> 00:04:41,050
If you can tell if his hand is covered
with Gyo when he grabs you,

51
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:45,840
it'll be simpler for you to know
which attack you should block.

52
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,220
So that's it.

53
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:50,560
You knew from my Gyo.

54
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:51,850
Cunning.

55
00:04:54,770 --> 00:04:56,350
Let me repeat myself.

56
00:04:57,000 --> 00:05:00,640
The shallow strategy you're using will backfire.

57
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:05,450
If you're caught by Little Flower when
you aren't using enough aura to defend,

58
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:10,870
a hit to the face will blow off your eyes,
nose, and mouth with no hope of repair.

59
00:05:11,310 --> 00:05:16,760
A hit to the arms or legs will incinerate skin,
severely damaging any nerves or muscle.

60
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,780
You'll have no fingers or toes left.

61
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:25,510
It's not possible for you to use Gyo to guard
against every attack that uses Gyo.

62
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,130
Now what?

63
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:30,850
I'm not interested in continuing this.

64
00:05:30,850 --> 00:05:33,270
Fighting you has made me see something...

65
00:05:33,610 --> 00:05:36,810
You have talent and a promising future.

66
00:05:36,810 --> 00:05:38,520
And many other chances.

67
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:44,000
Don't you think it's meaningless to throw
all that away just for your pride?

68
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:47,530
Just give up, stupid kid!

69
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:52,830
If he makes like he's going to use
both hands to blow you up,

70
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,390
that's a red light.

71
00:05:54,390 --> 00:05:57,410
Then it'll be time to stick to the plan.

72
00:05:58,180 --> 00:06:00,920
Sorry, Bisky and Killua.

73
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:04,140
I'm gonna be selfish here.

74
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:06,280
I have to give it a try...

75
00:06:06,620 --> 00:06:09,490
Because I just had a great idea!

76
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:13,430
If you seriously mean that,

77
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,810
you should surrender, Genthru!

78
00:06:19,490 --> 00:06:20,720
A shame...

79
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:25,820
Let me show you

80
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:31,240
that there are some things worse than death.

81
00:06:32,710 --> 00:06:35,280
I'll blow up both your arms.

82
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:38,260
Use Gyo to protect the one you want to keep.

83
00:06:38,260 --> 00:06:42,580
After that, I'll blow up your
remaining arm and left leg.

84
00:06:42,580 --> 00:06:45,020
Use Gyo to protect the one you want to keep.

85
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:47,590
And so on...

86
00:06:47,590 --> 00:06:49,980
Until you're out of limbs.

87
00:06:49,980 --> 00:06:51,930
Go ahead and try!

88
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:53,520
Very well.

89
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,180
Take this!

90
00:07:07,710 --> 00:07:10,510
Wh-What happened?

91
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:16,490
Blood?

92
00:07:17,430 --> 00:07:18,390
Damage?

93
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,680
He landed a hit?

94
00:07:21,550 --> 00:07:23,930
First comes rock!

95
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:25,880
Crap...

96
00:07:26,460 --> 00:07:28,260
Move... Dodge!

97
00:07:28,550 --> 00:07:29,380
Rock...

98
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:30,880
Paper...

99
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,210
Rock!

100
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,480
Did he hit me?

101
00:07:42,820 --> 00:07:44,950
No, I tripped.

102
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:48,030
What was that?

103
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:49,460
What just happened?

104
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,780
Now I understand...

105
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:56,870
Th-This kid...

106
00:07:57,260 --> 00:07:59,180
He sacrificed both hands!

107
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:05,830
But the damage wasn't distributed evenly!

108
00:08:06,510 --> 00:08:08,820
He probably gave up completely on his left hand,

109
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:11,860
protected his right hand with 30% of his aura,

110
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:15,520
and focused the remaining 70% on his legs...

111
00:08:17,010 --> 00:08:19,030
to attack me!

112
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:23,900
I use aura both to explode targets and
to shield my hand from the blast.

113
00:08:24,380 --> 00:08:27,000
If I use it on both hands,

114
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,080
I won't have much left for the rest of myself.

115
00:08:30,080 --> 00:08:31,490
He took advantage of that!

116
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:36,120
Still, no one sane would actually try that!

117
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:40,130
I gave him a pretty good scare!

118
00:08:43,380 --> 00:08:44,940
Damn...

119
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:47,030
This hurts like hell.

120
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:48,480
But...

121
00:08:49,670 --> 00:08:50,630
I'm going for it!

122
00:08:53,020 --> 00:08:54,630
I'm done...

123
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,800
He's done?

124
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,890
Is he giving up?

125
00:08:58,660 --> 00:08:59,950
Of course...

126
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,640
That makes sense.

127
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:04,720
He's lost his left hand,
and his right is badly injured.

128
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:08,050
And he managed to land a hit on me.

129
00:09:08,050 --> 00:09:10,520
He must be satisfied now.

130
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:13,030
I'm done being selfish...

131
00:09:14,330 --> 00:09:15,900
Time to get serious!

132
00:09:16,730 --> 00:09:18,780
Let's do this, Genthru!

133
00:09:20,070 --> 00:09:22,290
Th-This kid's

134
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,620
totally insane!

135
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,440
Book!

136
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,320
A card?

137
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:37,860
He shouldn't have anything to concern me.

138
00:09:39,590 --> 00:09:41,200
The card transformed?

139
00:09:41,490 --> 00:09:43,090
Paladin's Necklace?!

140
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:45,270
What is he planning?

141
00:09:46,190 --> 00:09:48,400
This is your last chance to surrender.

142
00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:53,810
Once I use this, you could end up dead.

143
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:56,150
You're clearly bluffing!

144
00:09:56,690 --> 00:09:57,910
Now wait...

145
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:59,660
This is my chance.

146
00:09:59,980 --> 00:10:00,950
Book.

147
00:10:01,890 --> 00:10:03,120
I give up.

148
00:10:03,480 --> 00:10:07,160
Obviously, you're never going to surrender.

149
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:08,670
Take them.

150
00:10:10,740 --> 00:10:12,600
I'll silence him.

151
00:10:12,890 --> 00:10:15,420
Crushing his windpipe and
knocking him out would be best.

152
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:19,180
Then I can take the cards from his binder.

153
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,440
I have one request.

154
00:10:21,740 --> 00:10:22,660
What is it?

155
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:25,780
Could you leave me this card?

156
00:10:32,130 --> 00:10:32,690
Bah...

157
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:35,440
He blocked my second attack with Gyo!

158
00:10:35,810 --> 00:10:38,080
But I did manage to crush his windpipe!

159
00:10:38,080 --> 00:10:42,010
He won't be able to use Book or Gain anymore.

160
00:10:44,210 --> 00:10:45,570
Genthru...

161
00:10:45,570 --> 00:10:49,080
You have made the worst mistake you could make.

162
00:10:49,790 --> 00:10:50,830
Gasoline
A glass container
filled with fuel.
Highly flammable.

163
00:10:51,710 --> 00:10:52,580
One minute!

164
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,090
What's that smell?

165
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:04,850
He can't use Little Flower any longer.

166
00:11:05,850 --> 00:11:07,600
I'm going to take him down!

167
00:11:07,890 --> 00:11:08,430
Book.

168
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:13,330
Oh, so this is gasoline...

169
00:11:13,330 --> 00:11:14,610
Very clever.

170
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:17,900
True, I cannot use Little Flower now...

171
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:20,360
However, I have another ability,

172
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,990
Countdown.

173
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:26,830
The ability that lets me set a bomb

174
00:11:26,830 --> 00:11:30,500
when I touch someone and say "Bomber."

175
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:34,990
The bomb can only be disarmed
by touching me and saying,

176
00:11:34,990 --> 00:11:37,500
"I caught the Bomber."

177
00:11:38,130 --> 00:11:41,160
This one is ten times stronger than Little Flower.

178
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:44,100
You won't be able to block it with Nen.

179
00:11:44,750 --> 00:11:47,450
All the activation requirements have been met.

180
00:11:48,090 --> 00:11:52,520
If I touch you and say, "Bomber,"
the countdown will begin.

181
00:11:53,100 --> 00:11:54,920
Try to run away...

182
00:11:54,920 --> 00:11:57,020
If you still have the strength.

183
00:11:57,470 --> 00:12:00,650
The requirements have been met... for me!

184
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:04,160
First comes rock...

185
00:12:05,690 --> 00:12:07,580
This is his earlier attack...

186
00:12:07,970 --> 00:12:09,660
If get too close, I'm done for.

187
00:12:10,380 --> 00:12:11,910
Is he trying to keep me back?

188
00:12:12,350 --> 00:12:13,330
Rock...

189
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:14,800
Paper...

190
00:12:15,630 --> 00:12:18,530
Rock!

191
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:26,760
A pitfall?

192
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,850
But he's falling with me!

193
00:12:41,970 --> 00:12:42,860
It's deep...

194
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:44,750
I can't climb back up.

195
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,880
But he should be in the same boat.

196
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:50,370
He's ended up cornering himself.

197
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,000
He's gone.

198
00:12:56,260 --> 00:12:57,730
Genthru...

199
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,380
If a card is removed from
the binder for a minute,

200
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:06,860
it reverts to an item.

201
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,560
Large Rock

202
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:14,890
A rock?!

203
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:36,930
First comes rock...

204
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,780
Rock...

205
00:13:40,780 --> 00:13:41,920
Paper...

206
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:43,760
W-W-Wait!

207
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,510
I surrender! I surrender!

208
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:49,590
Rock!

209
00:14:03,370 --> 00:14:04,320
Osu!

210
00:14:13,670 --> 00:14:14,700
Are you awake?

211
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:17,410
Summon your binder.

212
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:21,150
We want you to return the cards you stole

213
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:23,160
from the people you backstabbed.

214
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,840
On one condition...

215
00:14:27,180 --> 00:14:30,840
Use Archangel to heal Bara.

216
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:33,820
We have a Clone card.

217
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:35,720
Don't worry.

218
00:14:36,430 --> 00:14:38,340
That was always part of the plan.

219
00:14:38,690 --> 00:14:42,610
We brought six copies of Clone.

220
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:48,240
Book...

221
00:14:52,110 --> 00:14:52,840
Gain!

222
00:15:03,310 --> 00:15:05,880
What is your wish?

223
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:10,630
We need you to heal his hands and throat.

224
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:13,640
Actually, can you just heal all his injuries?

225
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:15,970
Easily done.

226
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:19,890
Then I shall heal his body.

227
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,250
I'm healed!

228
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:36,920
Then, farewell.

229
00:15:36,920 --> 00:15:38,860
All right!

230
00:15:40,230 --> 00:15:43,540
Okay, here's the extra Archangel.

231
00:15:47,060 --> 00:15:47,960
Gain!

232
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,670
Next up is Killua.

233
00:15:57,420 --> 00:16:00,650
Genthru, we're going to use your binder.

234
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,560
Go ahead.

235
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,640
Clone on!

236
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:09,510
Breath of Archangel has reached
its maximum card limit.

237
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:11,200
Clone will be destroyed.

238
00:16:13,810 --> 00:16:15,290
W-W-Wait!

239
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:16,420
What's going on?!

240
00:16:16,420 --> 00:16:17,960
Did I do something wrong?

241
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,790
No, it's Goreinu.

242
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:20,450
Huh?

243
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:25,270
He used Clone or Transform to increase the
number of Breath of Archangel vouchers.

244
00:16:25,950 --> 00:16:29,960
So two of his vouchers became
Breath of Archangel cards.

245
00:16:32,380 --> 00:16:36,290
Another player has used Contact to reach you.

246
00:16:36,780 --> 00:16:38,660
Yo, it's Goreinu.

247
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,980
Looks like you won.

248
00:16:43,060 --> 00:16:44,480
But I don't approve of this.

249
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:48,770
If you plan to use Breath of Archangel
to heal these murderers,

250
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:50,230
the trade is off!

251
00:16:50,660 --> 00:16:51,890
You okay with using it on me?

252
00:16:51,890 --> 00:16:53,090
Of course.

253
00:16:53,820 --> 00:16:55,610
I am an assassin.

254
00:16:55,610 --> 00:16:56,550
Eh?

255
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:58,870
I've killed more people than these guys.

256
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:03,670
Each player in this game risks their
life in one way or another.

257
00:17:04,110 --> 00:17:06,480
That doesn't make it okay to kill others.

258
00:17:06,870 --> 00:17:11,870
But all the people I've killed were
not nearly as prepared to die.

259
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,510
I'm worse than these guys.

260
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:17,810
No, you aren't like them.

261
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:21,800
I like you, but I hate their guts!

262
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,670
That isn't a valid reason!

263
00:17:23,670 --> 00:17:24,910
I don't need a reason...

264
00:17:24,910 --> 00:17:26,270
What counts is how I feel.

265
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,480
Aren't you guys the same way?

266
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:30,770
But we don't think it's right

267
00:17:30,770 --> 00:17:34,130
to let them die because we hate them.

268
00:17:35,120 --> 00:17:37,630
In battle, both sides risk their lives,

269
00:17:37,630 --> 00:17:40,240
and are prepared to kill.

270
00:17:40,870 --> 00:17:44,660
But that doesn't apply once the fight is over.

271
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:50,040
I haven't forgiven Genthru for
killing all those players...

272
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:53,900
But the three of us agreed before the fight

273
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:56,430
that we'd bring six Clone cards.

274
00:17:57,300 --> 00:18:00,550
I don't really remember why we decided that,

275
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:03,810
but it wasn't based on logic or reason.

276
00:18:04,740 --> 00:18:07,060
It was just the decision that came naturally to us.

277
00:18:07,480 --> 00:18:11,160
Once the fight was over and we'd
obtained Breath of Archangel,

278
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:13,570
we planned to heal everyone.

279
00:18:14,180 --> 00:18:17,710
All three of us made the decision,
so we wanted to stick to it.

280
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:21,830
But I understand how you feel,
and we can't change your mind.

281
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:23,700
Sorry, Killua...

282
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:26,250
Could you wait a little longer?

283
00:18:26,690 --> 00:18:28,050
No problem.

284
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:30,080
I'll recover on my own in a while.

285
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:37,330
The situation's changed, so we
can't use Clone anymore.

286
00:18:37,700 --> 00:18:40,030
There's only one Breath of Archangel left.

287
00:18:40,330 --> 00:18:43,720
Only one? Isn't that the original?

288
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,600
Use it on Genthru.

289
00:18:47,610 --> 00:18:49,170
I'm fine...

290
00:18:56,860 --> 00:18:59,860
Okay, let's use Accompany to go to Masadora.

291
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,210
Yeah.

292
00:19:01,210 --> 00:19:02,740
Hey, wait up...

293
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:06,250
Fine, you can have Breath of Archangel.

294
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:07,220
Huh?

295
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:09,210
Really? Are you sure?

296
00:19:09,210 --> 00:19:10,600
Yeah, actually...

297
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:14,300
Before you told me all this,
I planned to give it to you.

298
00:19:14,300 --> 00:19:17,630
Not just Archangel, but all of our cards.

299
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:18,680
What?!

300
00:19:18,680 --> 00:19:22,390
Tsezgerra, his team, and I all agreed.

301
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:25,700
We've decided to give up on the game.

302
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,900
Wow, I'm completely healed!

303
00:19:32,770 --> 00:19:34,820
Oh, so Mr. Battera...

304
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:38,900
Yeah, he paid Tsezgerra and his
team for breaking his promise.

305
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:40,770
I got four billion out of it.

306
00:19:40,770 --> 00:19:41,910
Four billion?!

307
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:42,850
Hey...

308
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:44,390
Share some of the wealth!

309
00:19:44,390 --> 00:19:45,920
Wh-What are you talking about?

310
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:48,920
Each of the four of us gets one billion!

311
00:19:49,250 --> 00:19:50,500
Eh?!

312
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:52,290
It's only fair...

313
00:19:52,290 --> 00:19:54,910
I couldn't have done this on my own.

314
00:19:54,910 --> 00:19:58,550
It was only possible because
I teamed up with you guys.

315
00:19:59,360 --> 00:20:01,440
I can't believe it...

316
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:04,800
You're such a nice guy!

317
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:08,310
Anyway, you can take all the cards.

318
00:20:08,940 --> 00:20:10,930
On one condition!

319
00:20:10,930 --> 00:20:14,210
You must be the first players to beat the game.

320
00:20:14,210 --> 00:20:15,030
Yep!

321
00:20:15,030 --> 00:20:15,940
Not a problem.

322
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:19,270
That gives you ninety-nine restricted slot cards.

323
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:22,200
Leaving only #0.

324
00:20:22,730 --> 00:20:24,020
One card to go...

325
00:20:24,420 --> 00:20:25,330
Yeah.

326
00:20:27,530 --> 00:20:31,170
Ninety-seven, ninety-eight...

327
00:20:31,790 --> 00:20:33,190
And this is...

328
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:36,340
Maid Panda
A species on the
verge of extinction.
Tidy, loves to cook,
and some individuals
enjoy Western clothing
and gardening.
Excellent at taking
care of human children.

329
00:20:34,580 --> 00:20:36,340
ninety-nine!

330
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:45,590
This announcement is for all players.

331
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:51,480
A player has collected ninety-nine
restricted slot cards.

332
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:55,660
Ten minutes from now, in honor of this event,

333
00:20:55,660 --> 00:21:01,610
there will be a quiz contest
for all Greed Island players.

334
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,560
There will be one hundred total questions

335
00:21:04,860 --> 00:21:07,620
dealing with restricted slot cards.

336
00:21:08,390 --> 00:21:12,370
The player who has the most
correct answers will receive

337
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:16,630
#0 Ruler's Blessing as a prize.

338
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:20,750
Please wait with your binders open.

339
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:24,440
Questions about restricted slot cards, huh?

340
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,880
I get it.

341
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:29,530
The questions are probably
designed so that players

342
00:21:29,530 --> 00:21:32,020
who mainly stole cards can't answer them.

343
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,370
Someone's coming!

344
00:21:35,850 --> 00:21:37,880
Wait, more over here!

345
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:49,640
The long battle has finally
reached its final stage.

346
00:23:01,150 --> 00:23:07,990
G.I. Tutorial

347
00:23:01,910 --> 00:23:04,840
Coming up, it's the
Greed Island Tutorial!

348
00:23:06,910 --> 00:23:08,900
Today, we introduce the card Transform.

349
00:23:07,990 --> 00:23:14,740
